Last Name: The abolitionist William Still organized this data as he aided freedom seekers in Philadelphia. Most records can be found in his 1872 book, The Underground Railroad. Some names are listed in "Journal C," an unpublished manuscript at the Historical Society of Pennsylvania.
First/Middle Name: Still's data was later compiled by James A. McGowan and William C. Kashatus and published in William C. Kashatus, William Still: The Underground Railroad and the Angel at Philadelphia (University of Notre Dame Press, 2021).
Alias: Data converted to Microsoft Excel Spreadsheet by Public Historian Nick Sacco. Email: pastexplore@gmail.com
